Use lemon juice and have patience



                        Posted by Reviewer2049460 on Jan 21, 2009
                     | Verified Purchase


This henna is excellent and very effective, especially for grays!  Don't listen to those comments with no patience or intelligence to read the directions...it will take a long time, so nuture yourself for a few hours and enjoy fantastic color...with no toxic chemicals.  As you use henna your hair will become darker over a few days, IF you use LEMON JUICE or another acidic such as vinegar.  Lemons smell better...Ginger or clove will reduce the odor of henna if you don't like the smell.  Do an internet search for henna use information if you're truly interested in nourishing yourself and your hair, instead of using a quick toxic fix.










