Light Mountain Mahogany



                        Posted by Reviewer3108583 on Jul 29, 2008
                     | Verified Purchase


If you are like me and concerned about the carcinogenic effects of using hair color this is a good alternative.  It is a two-step process and you have to allow time for the henna to cure so it takes a little more time than regular coloring—so plan accordingly. I did not have all the chemical residue from the last coloring out of my hair so the color came out with more gold tones that mahogany but still a nice color.  I got good grey hair coverage and my hair felt soft and conditioned, not brittle and dried out like with regular hair color. 










