Amazing Nutritive Ingredients


 


 
 
 
 
 


 
 
Comfrey Root Extract   (Symphytum officinale)It is a perennial plant with hairy stems and leaves, and can grow up to a height of two to five feet. The flowers can be white, creamy yellow, purple and red. Vitamin A and C are abundant in Comfrey. Besides, these essential vitamins, it is also rich in minerals such as calcium, potassium, phosphorus, magnesium, copper, zinc, and selenium. Comfrey roots and leaves are said to provide nutritive healing properties for all different types of ailments because of its high allantoin along with other substances that reduce inflammation and keep skin healthy.Horsetail Extract   (Equisetum arvense)It probably got its name due to its likeness to a horse's tail. In fact, the origin of its Latin name Equisetum, a combination of 'equs' meaning 'horse' and 'seta' meaning 'bristle' could be attributed to this resemblance. This relative of the fern is a descendant of large plants that grew on earth, some 270 million years ago. Silica in horsetail extract is thought not only to slow down hair loss in both men and women, but also encourages growth of new hair follicles. Horsetail extract helps to increase blood circulation, nourishes hair follicles and assist hair growth. The amino acids and phytosterols in horsetail help strengthen hair follicles while also reducing oil buildup on the scalp.Guava Leaf Extract   (Psidium guajava)Guava leaves has been traditionally used throughout history by many folk cultures. It can be used on damaged skin, acne, skin inflammations, irritation and itching. It is beneficial for fading blemishes and clearing dandruff. This leaf can be used on skin, scalp and hair. These leaves contain a number of beneficial substances, including antioxidants like vitamins A, C, B, K, Beta carotene, iron, calcium, potassium, phosphorus, and flavonoids such as quercetin. Guava leaves contain powerful antibacterial compounds that work well for skin and scalp infections. It may help with inflammation and itching from dandruff.Banaba Extract   (Lagerstroemia speciosa)Banaba is a species of crepe myrtle tree that is native to Southeast Asia. It is believed that the leaves of banaba have therapeutic properties. Banaba Leaf Extract contains a compound known as Corosolic acid which is reputed for topical use to reduce lipid content of skin.Nettle Root Extract   (Urtica dioica)Nettle Root has been used since ancient times as a hair treatment, growth stimulant, and to help restore nutritive hair color and shine. It is said that the ancient Greeks, Romans and the native tribes of America, had used this herb for medicinal purposes. The root contains polysaccharides and lignans that have an effect similar to steroid hormones. It may that may possess antiviral properties and acts as an anti-inflammatory.  Plantain Extract  (Plantago major)Native Americans carried powdered roots of Plantain as protection against snake bites. The herb has a long history of use as an alternative medicine dating back to ancient times. Plantain contains allantoin which is an anti-inflammatory that kills germs, helps healing, and stimulates the growth of new skin cells thus benefiting your scalp and follicles.Burdock Root Extract   (Arctium lappa)It is popularly known as 'oriental ginseng' in Japan. The plant has large leaves and purple flowers resembling thistle flowers. The root of the plant is used for cosmetic and medicinal purposes, including promoting healthy hair. Burdock makes hair healthy by improving scalp circulation. It improves the strength and helps with hair loss. Burdock root is a very nutritious it contains a high amount of Vitamins A, C, B1, E, and K.Apple Cider Vinegar   (Malus domestica)Apple cider vinegar contains the mother of vinegar and is made using only the best freshly-pressed apples. The apple cider vinegar is raw, unfiltered and unpasteurized, preserving the fragile essential nutrients. It can inhibit bacteria, mold and germs, yet it is environmentally safe. Apple Cider Vinegar has been highly regarded throughout history. In 400 B.C. the great Hippocrates, Father of Medicine, used it for its amazing health qualities. It contains valuable enzymes, botanical acids and vitamins. Its nutritive acidity discourages build-up on the scalp and adjusts skin pH when applied topically. The acidity of apple cider vinegar changes the pH of your scalp, so it’s not an ideal environment for yeast that can cause dandruff to grow. Vinegar has been used for decades to help with dandruff.Aloe Vera   (Aloe barbadensis)Aloe Vera has been used for improving skin conditions as the ancient Egyptians called it the “plant of immortality.” A succulent plant with rejuvenating and soothing properties, aloe vera holds many benefits for the skin. It has been used topically for thousands of years to improve skin conditions. It contains vitamins A, C, E, B1, B2, B3, B6, and B12. Aloe Vera also contains over 200 other naturally occurring nutrients such as enzymes, amino acids and sterols. Aloe gel is extracted from the leaves of the plant and when applied to the skin, softens dead skin cells leaving the skin feeling soft and smooth.
 
 


 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 


 
 
 
 
 
 


 






















 













 





 











 
 
 
 
 


